SIMPLE: indirectly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indirectly
<hw>In`di*rect"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In an direct
manner; not in a straight line or course; not in express terms;
obliquely; not by direct means; hence, unfairly; wrongly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To tax it <qex>indirectly</qex> by taxing their expense.</q>
<rj><qau>A. Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your crown and kingdom <qex>indirectly</qex> held.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indirectness</ent>⟦br⟧
